This paper deals with machine learning and natural language processing techniques applied to electronic medical records (EMRs) for predictive tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The paper also discusses neural models and attention mechanisms, which are common topics in the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with predictive tasks, which falls under the sub-category cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of EMRs, which could fall under the sub-category cs.CY (Computers and Society) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
